PRODUCT DESCRIPTION (Max 200 characters: Choose between two great rewards programs- Altitude Rewards or Altitude Qantas and enjoy the convenience of a platinum concierge service as well as a range of complimentary insurance covers
REWARDS DESCRIPTION (bullet points):
-If you choose Altitude Rewards:
'--2 Altitude Points - Altitude Platinum American Express&trade Card
'--1 Altitude Point - Altitude Platinum Visa Card
'--For each statement cycle a points cap of 7,500 Altitude Points applies when using either or both cards. Bonus points do not count towards the points cap.
'-If you choose Altitude Qantas:
'--1 Qantas Point - Altitude Platinum American Express™ Card
'--0.5 Qantas Points - Altitude Platinum Visa Card
'--For each statement cycle a points cap of 3,750 Qantas Points applies when using either or both cards. Bonus points do not count towards the points cap.
INTEREST RATE TERMS AND CONDITIONS:
-New cards only. Apply between 6 January 2015 and 19 April 2015.
'-Switches, upgrades, customers accessing employee benefits or packaged cards are ineligible for this offer
'-Introductory rate on purchases is not available in conjunction with any promotion other than the special balance transfer promotion available at card application
'-After 6 months, the introductory purchase rate will switch to the variable purchase rate then applicable to your card account.
[Consumer Credit Cards - Conditions of Use](http://www.westpac.com.au/docs/pdf/pb/Consumer_Conditions_of_use.pdf)
REWARDS TERMS AND CONDITIONS: [Altitude Rewards and Altitude Qantas Terms and Conditions](http://www.westpac.com.au/docs/pdf/pb/credit-cards/Altitude_Rewards_Terms_and_1.pdf)
BALANCE TRANSFER TERMS AND CONDITIONS:
-The promotional balance transfer rate is available when you apply for a new card between 6 January 2015 and 19 April 2015 and request at application to transfer balance(s) from up to 3 non-Westpac Australian issued credit, charge or store cards.
'-The variable cash advance rate will apply to balance(s) transferred but left unpaid at the end of the promotional period and to balance transfers requested at any time after card application.
'-Switches, upgrades, customers accessing employee benefits or packaged cards are ineligible
'-The balance transfer rate is not available in conjunction with any other promotion unless specified
'-Balance transfer rate will apply to any balance(s) transferred (min $200 up to 95% of your approved available credit limit) for the promotional period, unless the amount is paid off earlier
'-Card activation will trigger the processing of the balance(s) transferred
'-Interest free days don't apply to balance transfers
'-Westpac will not be responsible for any delays that may occur in processing payment to your other card account(s) and will not close the account(s).
